def: Pertaining to, or furnishing, a diagnosis; indicating thenature of a disease.
To discover or show one's self. [Obs.]This done, they discover. DeckeNor was this the first time that they discovered to be followers ofthis world. Milton.
Situated between the external and internal carotid arteries;as, an intercarotid ganglion.
An order of brachiopods, in which the valves of shell are notarticulated by a hinge. It includes the Lingula, Discina, and alliedforms. [Written also Lyopoma.]
Tending to exaggerate; involving exaggeration. "Exaggerativelanguage." Geddes. "Exaggerative pictures." W. J. Linton.-- Ex*ag"ger*a*tive*ly, adv. Carlyle.
A plant whose roots are fancied to resemble teeth, as certainplants of the genus Lathr√¶a, and various species of Dentaria. SeeCoralwort.
Northern; pertaining to the north, or to the north wind; as, aboreal bird; a boreal blast.So from their own clear north in radiant streams, Bright over Europebursts the boreal morn. Thomson.
Of or pertaining to the world; worldly; earthly; terrestrial;as, the mundane sphere.-- Mun"dane*ly, adv.The defilement of mundane passions. I. Taylor.
Any one of several species of large sting rays belonging toTrygon and allied genera.
